The paper discusses the integration of two important reasoning methodologies in artificial intelligence, namely rule-based reasoning and case-based reasoning. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of similarity measures and distance metrics, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The financial domain of mergers and acquisitions is used as an example, which falls under the category of computational economics (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of a prototype system, which involves software engineering and programming (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data structures and algorithms for efficient reasoning, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
